## 🔄 Procedura Deploy Corretta

### 1. Pre-Deploy: Verifica Stato Server

```powershell
# Connetti al server
$cred = Get-Credential
New-PSDrive -Name "S" -PSProvider FileSystem -Root "\\192.168.1.230\c$" -Credential $cred

# Verifica processi in esecuzione
Get-Process -ComputerName 192.168.1.230 -Name "MESManager*" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

# Oppure sulla macchina locale verso server
Invoke-Command -ComputerName 192.168.1.230 -Credential $cred -ScriptBlock {
    Get-Process -Name "MESManager*" | Select Name, Id, StartTime
}
```

### 2. Build Locale

```powershell
# Dalla root del progetto
cd C:\Dev\MESManager

# Build solution completo
dotnet build MESManager.sln -c Release

# Publish singolo progetto (framework-dependent)
dotnet publish MESManager/MESManager.Web/MESManager.Web.csproj -c Release -o publish/Web --self-contained false

# Publish con self-contained (include .NET runtime ~60MB extra)
dotnet publish MESManager/MESManager.Web/MESManager.Web.csproj -c Release -r win-x64 -o publish/Web --self-contained true
```

### 3. Stop Servizi (Ordine Importante!)

```powershell
# Sul server, ordine: PlcSync → Worker → Web
# Questo evita errori di SignalR e connessioni PLC orfane

# Metodo 1: Script già presente sul server
\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\stop-all-services.cmd

# Metodo 2: PowerShell remoto
Invoke-Command -ComputerName 192.168.1.230 -Credential $cred -ScriptBlock {
    # Stop PlcSync prima (ha connessioni PLC)
    taskkill /F /IM MESManager.PlcSync.exe 2>$null
    Start-Sleep -Seconds 5
    
    # Stop Worker
    taskkill /F /IM MESManager.Worker.exe 2>$null
    Start-Sleep -Seconds 2
    
    # Stop Web
    taskkill /F /IM MESManager.Web.exe 2>$null
    
    # Se IIS: iisreset /stop
}
```

### 4. Copia File (CON ESCLUSIONI!)

```powershell
# ⚠️ IMPORTANTE: Escludi i file di configurazione!

$excludeFiles = @(
    "appsettings.Secrets.json",
    "appsettings.Database.json", 
    "appsettings.Development.json",
    "*.log",
    "*.pdb"
)

# Copia Web
$source = "C:\Dev\MESManager\publish\Web\*"
$dest = "\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\Web\"

Get-ChildItem $source -Recurse | 
    Where-Object { $_.Name -notin $excludeFiles } |
    ForEach-Object {
        $targetPath = $_.FullName.Replace($source.TrimEnd('*'), $dest)
        Copy-Item $_.FullName -Destination $targetPath -Force
    }

# Oppure usa robocopy (più robusto)
robocopy "C:\Dev\MESManager\publish\Web" "\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\Web" /E /XF appsettings.Secrets.json appsettings.Database.json *.log *.pdb /XD SyncBackups
```

### 5. Riavvio Servizi (Ordine Inverso!)

```powershell
# Ordine: Web → Worker → PlcSync

# Metodo 1: Script sul server
\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\start-all-services.cmd

# Metodo 2: Manuale
Invoke-Command -ComputerName 192.168.1.230 -Credential $cred -ScriptBlock {
    Set-Location C:\MESManager
    $env:ASPNETCORE_ENVIRONMENT = "Production"
    $env:ASPNETCORE_URLS = "http://0.0.0.0:5156"
    
    # Avvia Web
    Start-Process "C:\MESManager\Web\MESManager.Web.exe" -WorkingDirectory "C:\MESManager\Web"
    Start-Sleep -Seconds 5
    
    # Avvia Worker  
    Start-Process "C:\MESManager\Worker\MESManager.Worker.exe" -WorkingDirectory "C:\MESManager\Worker"
    Start-Sleep -Seconds 3
    
    # Avvia PlcSync
    Start-Process "C:\MESManager\PlcSync\MESManager.PlcSync.exe" -WorkingDirectory "C:\MESManager\PlcSync"
}
```

### 6. Verifica Post-Deploy

```powershell
# Verifica processi attivi
Invoke-Command -ComputerName 192.168.1.230 -Credential $cred -ScriptBlock {
    Get-Process -Name "MESManager*" | Select Name, Id, StartTime
}

# Test connessione web
Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "http://192.168.1.230:5156" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 10

# Verifica log recenti
Get-Content "\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\Web\logs\startup.log" -Tail 20
Get-Content "\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\PlcSync\output.log" -Tail 20
```

