## 🔧 Comandi Rapidi per Copilot

Quando l'utente chiede di fare deploy, usa questi comandi:

### Deploy Completo (Tutti i Servizi)
```powershell
cd C:\Dev\MESManager
$psexec = "$env:TEMP\PsExec64.exe"

# 1. Build
dotnet publish MESManager.Web/MESManager.Web.csproj -c Release -o publish/Web --self-contained false
dotnet publish MESManager.Worker/MESManager.Worker.csproj -c Release -o publish/Worker --self-contained false
dotnet publish MESManager.PlcSync/MESManager.PlcSync.csproj -c Release -o publish/PlcSync --self-contained false

# 2. Stop servizi
& $psexec \\192.168.1.230 cmd /c "taskkill /F /IM MESManager.PlcSync.exe"
& $psexec \\192.168.1.230 cmd /c "taskkill /F /IM MESManager.Worker.exe"
& $psexec \\192.168.1.230 cmd /c "taskkill /F /IM MESManager.Web.exe"
Start-Sleep -Seconds 3

# 3. Copia file
robocopy publish/Web "\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\Web" /MIR /XF appsettings.Secrets.json appsettings.Database.json appsettings.Production.json /XD wwwroot\uploads
robocopy publish/Worker "\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\Worker" /MIR /XF appsettings.Secrets.json appsettings.Database.json
robocopy publish/PlcSync "\\192.168.1.230\c$\MESManager\PlcSync" /MIR /XD Configuration /XF appsettings.Database.json appsettings.Secrets.json

# 4. Riavvia servizi
& $psexec \\192.168.1.230 cmd /c "cd /d C:\MESManager\Web && start start-web.cmd"
& $psexec \\192.168.1.230 cmd /c "cd /d C:\MESManager\Worker && start start-worker.cmd"
& $psexec \\192.168.1.230 cmd /c "cd /d C:\MESManager\PlcSync && start start-plcsync.cmd"
```

### Deploy Solo Web
